name: Nacho Mamas Bean Dip
author: Lisa Ermgodts
summary: This is a great way to get your kids to eat beans and you will love it as well! You can add extra onions and canned or fresh jalapeno peppers to taste, but my kids love it this way!
ingredients: 1 (16 ounce) package sharp Cheddar cheese, chopped
½ (8 ounce) package reduced-fat cream cheese
1 (15 ounce) can ranch-style beans (such as Ranch Style®)
1 (15.5 ounce) can pinto beans with jalapeno peppers and bacon (such as Trappey's®), drained
1 (10.5 ounce) bag scoop-shaped corn chips (such as Fritos® Scoops)
directions: Pulse Cheddar cheese and green onions together in a blender until evenly chopped; add cream cheese and pulse until blended
Pour in ranch-style beans; pulse to blend
Blend in pinto beans and cilantro until smooth
